8. Annual return
(1) Every registered society shall, not later than 18 months after its date of registration, and subsequently every year from date of first return, furnish the Registrar with an annual return giving a true and fair view of the state of the financial affairs of the society in accordance with Form F set out in Schedule 1.
(1A) The annual return referred to in subregulation (1) shall be accompanied by—
( a ) minutes of meeting;
( b ) membership list;
( c ) signed attendance register;
( d ) annual financial statement from bank or other regulated financial channels;
( e ) comprehensive financial report; and
( f ) security clearance report from any law enforcement agency.
(2) Every office-bearer shall ensure that the annual return referred to under subregulation (1) is duly furnished to the Registrar.

12. Arbitration of disputes
(1) Where there exists a dispute within a registered society between members of a registered society or between a registered society and another, a member of a registered society or a registered society as the case may be, may lodge a dispute with the Registrar in accordance with Form H set out in Schedule 1.
(1A) Where a dispute is lodged in accordance with subregulation (1), the submission shall contain—
( a ) the particulars of the parties to the dispute;
( b ) the nature of the dispute;
( c ) the summary of the dispute;
( d ) proof that internal dispute resolution mechanism and any other dispute resolution structures have been exhausted; and
( e ) any supporting documents.
(2) The Registrar shall, where the dispute is lodged in accordance with subregulation (1), refer the dispute for arbitration by the Advisory and Arbitration Council, in accordance with Form I set out in Schedule 1.

13A. Re-registration of existing societies
(1) Any existing society shall, in accordance with section 32(1), apply for registration in Form A set out in Schedule 1.
(2) An application for re-registration under this regulation shall be accompanied by a society’s—
( a ) membership list;
( b ) Constitution;
( c ) registration certificate or number;
( d ) office-bearers;
( e ) place of operation;
( f ) contact information;
( g ) financial returns of the year preceding the re-registration; and
( h ) list of branches indicating physical addresses.
